Some linux Commands cheatsheet

To remove a repo:

	1. repos list usually stays in the /etc/apt folder under the file sources.lists
	2. to remove a repos for example with a name http://ppa.launchpad.net/shutter/ppa/ubuntu 
	3. sudo apt-add-repository -r ppa:shutter/ppa
	4. sudo apt update -q

To create an alias in linux
	1. Go to the root directory and open the .bashrc file.
	2. inside type 
	alias = prefferedAliasName="the command you want to run"

To restart the plasma desktop enviornment "Gracefully"
	1. sudo kquitapp5 plasmashell
	2. sudo kstart5 plasmashell   

To setup sstp client

    1. $ sudo add-apt-repository ppa:eivnaes/network-manager-sstp
...
    2. $ sudo apt-get update
    3. $ sudo apt-get install sstp-client
    4. $ sudo apt-get install network-manager-sstp-gnome # NM configuration GUI
